{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"wig-grove-eye","description":"# Elevate trust-boundary crossing to an explicit framing in the T5c plan-review security overlay\n\n## Context\nFollow-up to a278 (container/leaf scrutiny + T10 endpoint-auth). Research on how mature\nsecurity / LLM-review projects avoid false positives converged on **trust-boundary crossing** as\nthe scope gate: a security concern is in scope only when a component is reachable by a LOWER-trust\nactor (STRIDE Spoofing↔authn; OWASP ASVS 1.4.1 enforcement points; Semgrep/Anthropic\nexploitability-over-category). Today T5c uses this idea only implicitly. Making it an explicit,\nfirst-class framing (a) generalizes beyond auth to T5c's other dimensions and (b) sharpens the\nreachability judgement — while keeping rebar's own local/in-process work false-positive-free.\nScope note: this is for **T5c only** — T10's `endpoint_access_contract` stays focused on infra\ncontract-completeness and must NOT be re-scoped to the general framing (approved: don't blur T10).\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5c.md` (rubric), `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json` (T5c checklist if needed).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `plan_review_T5c.md` leads with an explicit TRUST-BOUNDARY scope gate: a security finding is in\n      scope only when the plan introduces/exposes a component reachable by a lower-trust actor\n      (public internet, another tenant, an untrusted network, an unauthenticated user); in-process /\n      local-CLI / loopback-only surfaces PASS as not-applicable.\n- [ ] The framing GENERALIZES beyond auth: the same gate governs T5c's existing dimensions\n      (authn/authz, encryption-in-transit, least-privilege, secret lifecycle) — each fires only where\n      a boundary is actually crossed.\n- [ ] Preserves the positive-pass carve-out (pure library / in-process module / single-user local CLI /\n      loopback-only → PASS, no auth demanded) so rebar's own local work stays FP-free.\n- [ ] Zero-trust caveat encoded: a single-tenant / private network is LOWER severity, not exempt.\n- [ ] T10 `endpoint_access_contract` is left unchanged (no blurring); a test/asserts T10 still fires\n      only on infra intent.\n- [ ] Validation: recalibrated T5c run against `d251` (or an equivalent networked-service plan)\n      surfaces the security surface via the trust-boundary gate; run against a local no-network\n      negative (`8a1c`/`4702`) PASSes as not-applicable — old-vs-new documented.\n- [ ] `validate-routing` + plan-review unit tests + `make lint` green.","id":"2e89-061c-1784-48c4","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Trust-boundary framing for the T5c plan-review security overlay (generalize the scope gate; keep T10 focused)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782906709407934001,"uuid":"048b0a37-a65f-41b7-af56-72db51de76e0"}